## 15. Limitations

| Limitation | Impact |
|-----------|--------|
| **Small knowledge base** | Only 15 documents — real systems need thousands |
| **No document chunking** | Real docs need splitting into overlapping chunks |
| **Simple retrieval** | Cosine similarity; production systems use HNSW/FAISS indices |
| **No reranking** | A reranker (cross-encoder) would improve retrieval precision |
| **No conversation memory persistence** | History is lost between sessions |

## 16. How to Improve

1. **Scale the knowledge base** — load real documentation
2. **Add a vector database** — ChromaDB or FAISS for efficient large-scale retrieval
3. **Add a reranker** — cross-encoder reranking after initial retrieval
4. **Chunk documents** — split long docs into overlapping 200-word chunks
5. **Add feedback loop** — let users rate answers to improve over time

## 17. Production Considerations

- **Latency:** Embedding + retrieval + LLM generation adds up. Cache frequent queries.
- **Cost:** Local LLM (Ollama) eliminates API costs.
- **Monitoring:** Log retrieval scores, answer lengths, and user feedback.
- **Updates:** Re-embed knowledge base when documents change.
#%% md
## 18. Common Mistakes & Key Takeaways

| Mistake | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| No retrieval — ask LLM directly | Always ground answers in retrieved documents |
| Too many documents in context | Retrieve top 2-3 only; more adds noise |
| No out-of-domain handling | Use retrieval score threshold to detect off-topic questions |
| Ignoring conversation history | Pass last 2-3 turns for coherent multi-turn dialogue |

| # | Takeaway |
|---|----------|
| 1 | **RAG > LLM-only** for domain-specific Q&A — grounding reduces hallucination |
| 2 | **Semantic retrieval** finds relevant docs even when phrasing differs |
| 3 | **System prompts** control answer style — minimal, structured, or strictly grounded |
| 4 | **Out-of-domain detection** via retrieval score prevents confident wrong answers |
| 5 | **Multi-turn context** makes conversations coherent |
| 6 | **Evaluation rubrics** make chatbot quality measurable |

